tic from the West side. There is enough room to kite on this side of the big isle, but it is tight (I always keep manaskin up, and it's saved me a couple times).<br><br>Using these techniques, I've had zero deaths in 3 levels of kiting here.  It helps a lot to have a reliable connection with a low ping time (mine is usually in the 75 range).  If my ping time is above 300 I start having problems.<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> A couple notes:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>- Respawn rate is 12 minutes, just about perfect for medding from oom to full.<br><br>- I don't recommend attempting raptors until you reach 54. You need Pillar of Lightning to do these safely.<br><br>- always keep levitate/jboots up. Being able to run out over the water to give you a bit of extra distance can be a lifesaver.<br><br>- don't kite in or over the water. Casting across the water boundary doesn't generally work, and in the water you lose your speed edge.<br><br>- if something goes wrong, run to chessboard isle and camp to clear agro. I know one wizard who just casts abscond -- I usually don't have the mana.<br><br>- none of the raptors can see invis. Use this to your advantage.  To safely be afk at a &quot;safe spot&quot; cast improved invis on yourself.<br><br>- there are enough spawns to support 3 people quadding here, with 3 left over if you really have a 4th. Share with those who appear -- there's usually more than enough to go around.  Also talk to people who are likely to be looking for raptors in TD.  You'll make some new friends, and they'll remember where you are so they don't train you (and vice versa).<br><br>- if there is someone camping here, they are usually taking the north side of the small isle. Learning how to do the big isle virtually guarantees you'll get a spot.  (Unless all have read this guide and know the secret of the big island.)<br><br>- if you are sharing with a druid, bear in mind that druid techniques generally take a bit longer than wizard techniques.  Cycle time for a wizard is about 15 minutes (2-3 min to kill, 12 respawn/med), for druids it is closer to 18-20.<br><br>- there is a BUG where sometimes raptors that are near death will warp back to their spawn point. Once there, they get their uber regen ability, so track them down and finish them off. If you are kiting them on their isle, this is easy. If you are kiting them on chessboard isle, this is a pain.<br><br>Happy hunting!<br><br>- Armok Komra <br>58 wizard of Povar <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A> at: 7/19/01 3:58:19 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufaiar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faiar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/01 2:46:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> When I was kiting raptors I always did the west side of the small isle. The roamer pops on this side so you won't have to wait for it. You kite the roamer, the 2 spawns on the west side and the VR on the nice long west beach. If the raptors become crowded, someone else can take the 2 spawns at the ruins + the single in the cove of the large island without disturbing your kiting. <p><img src="http://splatfisk.dk/uber.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uailwyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailwyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/30/01 4:08:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> Thanks guys! This will help me out a lot.<br><br>~Ailwyn 54th wizurp <br>{Pravus Dei} Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uquuasi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quuasi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/16/01 10:15:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> thanks, i've never seen it written out like this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucuellar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuellar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/01 10:27:14 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/images/battle/diablo2/images/animations/bestiary/act1/Andariel.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> The warp occurs if you move out of agro range.<br><br>Usually if something is snared, stops, but you keep running, it will sometimes warp back home. <br><br>-Cueller <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uetheon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Etheon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/01 8:50:50 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/erichq2/penguin.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> I could kite them at 51 easily with pillar of frost, so its doable. <p><body vlink="#0000FF" alink="#0000FF"><div align="center"><img src=http://members.aol.com/erichq2/etheon.jpg width="474" height="75"><br>Etheon, 55<sup>th</sup> lvl Evoker<br><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Profile=0&Id=12035>Profile</a> | <a href=http://www.veilofsilence.org>Veil of Silence</a> | <a href=http://www.innoruuk.com>Innoruuk</a> | <a href=mailto:EricHQ2@aol.com>E-Mail</a></div><p><FONT color=#000000 face=Antiqua size=1 Book><B>Palop went to the dam, to get some dam water, but the dam man said Palop couldn't have any dam water. So Palop said, Fine, keep your own dam water. -Palop</B></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 3:28:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> Success in kiting raptors at 51 with Pillar of Frost depends a bit on your mana gear and your skill in dealing with the inevitable resists and other unexpected events.  I talked to one wizard the other day who starting working raptors at 52 and he reported a blown kite (running to chessboard and camping out to clear agro) on about 1 in 5 pulls.  Whether this is acceptable to you or not is a personal decision, but be aware that if others are kiting raptors, their return might disrupt another player's pattern -- so communicate with others hanging out here.<br><br>My recommendation for someone attempting raptors at 51 would be to avoid the VR spawns if at all possible.  The easiest way to do this is to kite the 3 on the south side of the small isle, and then grab a 4th either from the big isle (coordinate this with whomever is doing big isle) or grabbing the loner at the north side of big isle.<br><br>If you can pull it off... the experience gains doing raptors at 51 would be truely insane.<br><br>- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>59 wizard of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umadleon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Madleon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 2:01:41 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> Thanx for the info. Sick of wyverns but CS is so perfect for quad kiting, with the hill to let u group them up. Quad kiting is easy for me but I don't have a flux stick so i aggro by range. This usually doesn't get me hurt but when I need to group them up, I sometimes get stunned and take a good whack (50% of health). I like to keep them full speed so I can ae snare them, is this doable at the Raptors? Doesn't seem like alot of room to move around to have them grouped, then even more space to space out their speed to my jboots speed. Either way, i am so there... <p><center><table width="50%" border="2" height="74" bordercolor="#FF0000" bgcolor="#000000">  <tr>    <td>      <div align="center"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="-2"><b>..<font color="#FF3333">         Mad @</font> <a href="http://www.packetlost.com">http://www.packetlost.com</a></b>         <b>..</b></font></div>    </td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td><a href="http://www.packetlost.com/"><img src="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/htsb.jpg" width="468" height="88" border="0"></a></td>  </tr></table></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 9:22:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> There is enough room to snare all four at once on each isle.  I usually have levitate up so that I can extend the &quot;runway&quot; a few extra feet.  Good runways include north and south side of small isle, and the eastern half of the south beach on big isle (running East/West).  If you are moderately careful, you can avoid getting hit entirely.  Resists are a major pain here, and you usually have to first snare the resistor, then walk out in to the water a ways to get them regrouped again.<br><br>Best of luck with these guys!  If you don't have flux staff, you'll find gathering them quite a bit easier because of their large agro range.<br><br>- Armok Komra (Arcis)<br>59 wizard of Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/18/01 9:28:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> &gt;I usually have levitate up<br><br>This is a key issue btw, if you don't always have levitate up you will get hit a lot. It also makes the breaking the big island a *lot* harder. It can be done (I did it once to see if I could when I was bored) but it makes things a lot harder than they need to be. Also, you can break the big island on either the east or west side (I usually do west because it is easier to do the vics there). If you do the west side, you actually end up with more straight space to kite in. <p>Qaman<BR>Sorcerer<BR>Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utegellan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tegellan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/22/01 1:59:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1>  an extra good thing about keeping lvi up at all times is that you can bunch them up very easily by running them into the water at the beginning of the kite, then just run along the coastline a little way out and when you run back up on the beach do a little circle and voila you are ready to snare in no time, also the water slows them down so it's easier to get some distance to them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br> <p> <i>Tegellan Fey`Brandhe</i><BR> Channeler<Br> The Circle of Eternity<BR> <a href="mailto:tegellan@hotmail.com">tegellan@hotmail.com</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urombusmindspire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Sorcerer</font></td></tr></table></span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(7/19/01 3:56:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/sidepic.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Armok's guide to Kiting Raptors</span><hr size=1> Moved to Library on July 19, 2001. <p><BR><BR><p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://wots-signatures.hypermart.net/rombus/rombus.gif" width="474" height="75" alig